comm - compare two sorted files line by line
sdiff - two files side by side
patch - apply a diff file to original
	patch < patch.diff - apply patch
	diff -u <old-filename> <new-filename> > patch.diff - create patch

SEARCH:
grep -v inverse, -n lineNumbers, -w wholeWord, -Ax or -Bx x lines after or before, -r recursive, -o, --only-matching (count occurrences with | wc -l), -P perl notation (if you need \t or .+), -I - do not process binary files, -l - just print files with matches, -L - just print files wihouth matches -e <pattern> - specify pattern (needed if it starts with -)
